Multiple credit cards, should I close accounts? Hello, I had pretty bad credit and I have been rebuilding it over the last several years. When I started this journey I could only get one of those cards that you have to put your own money down first and that is your limit, and now I can be approved for cards with limits like $5000. 

&amp;#x200B;

Hypothetically let's say that I had 3 high-interest low benefit cards carrying a $0 balance, and 2 mid-low interest cards with benefits like airline points that I use for emergency/purchases. I am not concerned about % of credit used because I will keep it at or under 20%, but I am unclear how the age of my accounts works. Would closing some or all of the 3 lower cards hurt my credit?
